    "plan_content": "The plan is complete. Here's a summary of what I designed:\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin Plan\n\n**14 new files** in `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files touched.\n\n### Architecture decisions:\n- **Single-account model** (like Nostr) — `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, config under `channels.pulseboard.*`\n- **Both `direct` + `group` chat types** — boards (`#board-name`) route as groups; usernames route as DMs\n- **4000-char text chunk limit** — set in `outbound.textChunkLimit`\n- **Fictional client stub** (`src/client.ts`) — typed `PulseboardClient` class with `sendDirectMessage` / `sendBoardMessage` / `connect` / `disconnect`; no real network calls since the platform doesn't exist\n\n### Key patterns followed:\n| Pattern | Source |\n|---|---|\n| Plugin entry points, manifest, package.json | Nostr (`extensions/nostr/`) |\n| `createChatChannelPlugin` + single-account config | Nostr `src/channel.ts` |\n| Group policy + board dispatch | IRC `src/inbound.ts` / `src/channel.ts` |\n| Setup wizard + adapter | Nostr `src/setup-surface.ts` |\n| `runtime-api.ts` barrel | Nostr (adapted — no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` path exists, so re-exports directly from general SDK subpaths) |\n\n### One item to verify at implementation time:\nThe exact SDK export path for `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` (used for group/board dispatch) — likely `openclaw/plugin-sdk/inbound-reply-dispatch`, but should be confirmed against the package.json `exports` map before writing the import.",
